title: MAFS: Martha and Michael transform into Kim and Kanye clones
text:
They're one of the most popular couples in Married At First Sight history.

But some fans believe Martha Kalifatidis and Michael Brunelli are taking their fame to new heights by transforming themselves into Australia's answer to Kim Kardashian and Kanye West.

Michael, a primary school teacher, has recently changed up his personal style, going from a European aesthetic to more of a hip hop vibe.

Twinning! Some fans believe Martha Kalifatidis and Michael Brunelli (L) are taking their fame to new heights by transforming themselves into Australia's Kim Kardashian and Kanye West (R)

Like Kanye, he now wears baggy shorts, T-shirts and sneakers.

Michael and Martha also took a trip to Los Angeles recently, where they dined at one of Kylie Jenner's favourite restaurants, Catch.

It's no secret that Martha, who once described herself as a 'Kmart Kardashian', is an admirer Kim's style and mannerisms.

Kids in America! Michael and Martha took a trip to Los Angeles recently, where they dined at one of Kylie Jenner's favourite restaurants, Catch

At the Logie Awards in June, Martha sashayed down the red carpet in a revealing two-piece ensemble that highlighted her slender midriff.

The unexpectedly angelic look, of course, bore a striking resemblance to a white outfit Kim wore to the Council of Fashion Designers of America Awards in 2018.

Unlike Kim, Martha has made no secret of her plastic surgery transformation.

New style: Michael, a primary school teacher, has recently changed up his personal style, going from a European aesthetic to more of a hip hop vibe

Reality TV role: Kanye occasionally appears on Keeping Up with the Kardashians with Kim

The makeup artist has undergone various procedures since she was 22, including a breast augmentation and a nose job.

She also regularly invests in non-surgical cosmetic treatments, like Botox and fillers.

'I do Botox but I like to keep it really understated and natural, so I don't like to look like I've had anything done,' Martha previously told NW magazine.
